"clear: both;"></div><div id="i23"><div>Training is crucial for organizational development and success. Training is beneficial to both employers and employees of organizations. Employees become more efficient and productive when they are trained well.</div></div><div class="hr"></div><div class="h2"><b>Training and Development Benefits </b></div><div id="i26"><div>There are numerous benefits to conducting employee training and development activities in your organization. These reasons include:</div><div><ul><li>Increased job satisfaction and morale among employees<br></li><li>Increased employee motivation<br></li><li>Increased efficiencies in processes, resulting in financial gain<br></li><li>Increased capacity to adopt new technologies and methods<br></li><li>Increased innovation in strategies and products<br></li><li>Reduced employee turnover</li><li>Risk management, e.g., training about sexual harassment, diversity training<br></li></ul></div></div><div class="hr"></div><div class="h2"><b>Our Process</b></div><div id="i29"><div style="background-color: inherit;"><span style="background-color: inherit;"><b>Step 1: Conduct A Needs Assessment</b></span><br><span style="background-color: inherit;">In this step, we will learn about your organization and identify the problems you hope to solve with a training and development system.</span><br><br><span style="background-color: inherit;"><b>Step 2: Design a Prototype</b></span><br><span style="background-color: inherit;">After identifying the goals for the training and development system, we will design a prototype program to test with a small, pilot group of employees.</span><br><br><span style="background-color: inherit;"><b>Step 3: Organizational Implementation</b></span><br><span style="background-color: inherit;">After we have perfected the prototype, we will then scale it up and implement the training and development system throughout your entire organization, usually progressing through one operating unit at a time.</span><br><br><span style="background-color: inherit;"><b>Step 4: Evaluate Effectiveness</b></span><br><span style="background-color: inherit;">At agreed upon intervals, we will evaluate the effectiveness of the training and development program that we have installed in your organization and make revisions and improvements where indicated.</span></div><div style="background-color: inherit;"><span style="background-color: inherit;"><br></span></div><div><a href="contact.php"><u>Contact us</u></a> today, and let us help you create a training and development program that will help you GROW your organization.<span style="background-color: inherit;"><br></span></div></div></div></div><div id="footer"><div id="footer0">Â© <span class="year">2017</span> - EDWARD PROFESSIONAL ADVISORS<div>info@edwardpa.com</div><div>888-858-9510<br></div></div></div></div><script type="text/javascript">document.body.onload = deferFonts;setTimeout(deferFonts, 2000);function deferFonts() { var defer = document.querySelectorAll("[defer]"); for (var i = 0; i < defer.length; i++) { defer[i].setAttribute("href", defer[i].getAttribute("defer")); }}</script><script type="text/javascript">var menuBtn = document.getElementById("menu-btn");menuBtn.addEventListener("touchstart", toggleMobileNav);var mobileMenu = document.getElementById("mobile-nav");function toggleMobileNav(event) { if (mobileMenu.style.display != "block") { mobileMenu.style.maxHeight = 0; mobileMenu.style.minHeight = mobileMenu.style.height = "auto"; mobileMenu.style.display = "block"; mobileMenu.className = "open-mobile-nav"; } else { mobileMenu.style.minHeight = mobileMenu.style.height = "auto"; mobileMenu.style.maxHeight = "50vh"; mobileMenu.className = "close-mobile-nav"; setTimeout(function() { mobileMenu.style.display = "none"; }, 400); }}var year = document.getElementsByClassName("year");var newDate = new Date();for (var x = 0; x < year.length; x++) { year[x].innerHTML = newDate.getFullYear();}</script></body></html>